transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, how can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Sir, I ordered a couple of months back, I guess 30 of your product, I paid for it by credit card, and I've gotten two unrequested replacements, which is really wrong, I've gotten two billings, not billings, can you keep sending it to me, and I did not authorize an open-ended use of my credit card.

Speaker 1: Yeah, did you take a look at the terms and conditions that were emailed to you after you placed your initial order?

Speaker 2: No, all I'm saying is I don't want it to happen.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I got it, no worries, I'm just explaining to you on the terms and conditions it states to you how all these prescriptions are through Pfizer, so they need a refill date to become active, without that refill date we wouldn't be able to approve your orders, so it looks like right now the doctor has you set up every month, this is Joseph Hayden, correct?

Speaker 2: That's right.

Speaker 1: Got it, so if you want I can just freeze out your account, that way you don't lose access to the prescription, because if I cancel it entirely, you won't be able to order this down the road when you require them again.

Speaker 2: Well, what I want you to do is just cancel my, not cancel my account, but just no longer send it to me on a monthly basis.

Speaker 1: Yeah, yeah, that's not a problem, we don't need to send it to you every month, what I can do is freeze it out for you, that way you can call us when you need it, and call us to delay it, and not get it at a monthly frequency, it sets it up for every six months.

Speaker 2: That's fine.

Speaker 1: Perfect, so we can go ahead and adjust that for you so you don't lose access to your VIP.

Speaker 2: Other than that, I made that modification to your account, you won't get another order monthly, and if you have any questions at all, just feel free to reach out to us, more than happy to help.

Speaker 1: Okay, and yeah, I'm glad you have a hotline, but most importantly, I'm not going to get any more unless I specifically order them, right?

Speaker 2: Yeah, you won't receive any more monthly, that's the reason why I made the modification to your order.

Speaker 1: Well, monthly, or bi-yearly, or anything else, right, in other words, I've now ordered, you know, one, I've now gotten a total of three, I want to see how it works.

Speaker 2: Yeah, call us when you require them again, and then we'll go ahead and help you out during that moment.

Speaker 1: Okay, very good.

Speaker 2: Yeah, no problem.

Speaker 1: Hope you have a good one, though.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
